Your Honor,

I stand before this honorable court today to take full responsibility for the offense in question. I am pleading guilty to the charge of speeding, as I understand the gravity of the situation and the potential harm I could have caused. 

I would like to first acknowledge that my actions were inexcusable and put not only myself but also others in danger. I regret the recklessness and the risk I posed to those around me. It is clear that I made a poor decision by testing the speed limits of my new car, and I understand the need to face the consequences of my actions.

I am aware that I failed to respond to the Notice of Intended Prosecution (NIP) that was sent to me. While I cannot deny my negligence in not reading my mail regularly, I want to assure the court that if I had received the notice, I would have promptly replied to it. I deeply regret this oversight and understand that it is a separate offense for which I must also plead guilty.

In considering my plea, I would like to bring to the court's attention some mitigating factors. Firstly, I am 26 years old and I acknowledge that my age does not fall within the typical range of 30 to 79 years. Secondly, although I have accumulated penalty points on my license from previous speeding incidents, I have no criminal record, which I believe demonstrates that this offense is an isolated incident. Furthermore, I suffer from ADHD, which may have influenced my impulsivity in this particular situation.

While I cannot change the past, I am committed to making amends for my actions. I understand the importance of compensating for any harm caused to others and I am willing to take any necessary steps to achieve this, whether it be through community service or financial restitution. Additionally, I have learned a valuable lesson from this experience and I am determined to never repeat this offense in the future. I am committed to seeking counseling and implementing strategies to better manage my ADHD, which may assist in preventing similar incidents from occurring again.

Moreover, I want to emphasize that the consequences of my actions have already had a significant impact on my life. The weight of my actions and the pending legal proceedings have caused me immense personal suffering and stress. I assure the court that I have taken this time to reflect upon my behavior and to better understand the consequences of my actions.

Finally, I would like to highlight my positive contributions to society. Outside of this incident, I have strived to be a law-abiding citizen. I have actively participated in community initiatives and have worked towards making a positive difference in the lives of others. I hope that the court takes this into consideration when weighing the appropriate punishment for my offense.

In conclusion, I respectfully request the court's leniency and understanding as I take responsibility for my actions. I am deeply remorseful for my reckless behavior and assure the court that I have learned from this experience. I am committed to making amends and preventing any future transgressions.

